  "body": "**Motivation**\r\nAll client implementations of the precompile `ecrecover` apparently check if the value `v` is 27 or 28. The references for the different client implementations can be found [here](https://github.com/ethereum/yellowpaper/pull/860).\r\n\r\nThere are two ways to deal with this IMHO:\r\n1. Either we remove the check [here](https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/blob/master/contracts/utils/cryptography/ECDSA.sol#L166), or\r\n2. we keep it with a custom error for better error reporting. In this case, we could even optimise it like that (if you are open to assembly):\r\n\r\n```solidity\r\nassembly {\r\n   ...\r\n    vIsInvalid := iszero(byte(v, 0x0000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000101000000))\r\n}\r\n```",
